Pre-Game Insights: The Braves look to sweep the 2-game series against the Nationals.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves won the first game 12-0.
The Nationals lead the season series 7-5.
The Braves have a 50-14 record in games when they did not give up a home run.
Others: The Braves' Max Fried (9-8, 3.35 ERA, 1.19 WHIP, 138 strikeouts) will face the Nationals' Jake Irvin (9-12, 4.28 ERA, 1.21 WHIP, 140 strikeouts).
